content:
Add a Time Input Element to a FlexCard

Available beginning Winter '22.

From the FlexCards tab, click a version of a FlexCard to open the FlexCard Designer.
From the Build panel, click Inputs, and drag the Time element onto the canvas.

Configure properties common to all Input elements:

In Field Binding, bind the value of the input element to an existing or new data field. 
In Field Label, enter the label that appears next to the element.
(Optional) In Placeholder, enter temporary text that displays inside the input field and which suggest to the user what content to enter.
(Optional) Check Required if the user must enter or select a value for this input element.
(Optional) Check Read-only to disable the ability to modify the input values.
(Optional) In Help Text, enter helpful text about the purpose of the input field.

In Default Value, select a default input value from a merge field. Or, enter a value as plain text in the format specified in Time Format.
Update the Time Format. 
To limit the user to a specific time range, set the Minimum Time and Maximum Time.

Select a time in the format specified in Time Format.
(Optional) In Time Interval, update the time intervals from the default 30 to another increment.
(Optional) To configure additional properties available to the element, click + Add New in the Custom Attributes section.
title: Adding a Time Input Element to a FlexCard
